<center><h1>String and Math Functions in JavaScript</h1></center>
<div class="op">
<center><h2><u> String function in javaScript </u></h2></center>
<p>Let the string str=<b>" web programming"</b>
<p><strong>  1. Length : </strong> <span id="len"></span> </p>
<p><strong>  2. Uppercase:</strong><span id="up"></p></span> </p>
<p><strong>  3. Lower case:</strong><span id="low"></p></span> </p>
<p><strong>  4. Character at (2) :</strong><span id="c_at"></p></span> </p>
<p><strong>  5. String at  [3] :</strong><span id="str"></p></span> </p>
<p><strong>  6. Index of "programming" :</strong><span id="index"></span> </p>
<p><strong>  7. Slice :</strong><span id="slice"></span></p>
<p><strong>  8. Split:</strong><span id="split"></span> </p>
<p><strong>  9. Concat str1="Good" and str2="Morning" :</strong><span id="concat"</span> </p>
<p><strong>  10. Repeat :</strong><span id="repeat"></span> </p>
<p><strong>  11. Replace :</strong><span id="replace"></span> </p>
</div>
<div class="math">
<center><h2><u> math function in javaScript </u></h2></center><br>
<p><strong>  1. Math.round(3.7) : </strong> <span id="round"></span></p>
<p><strong>  2. Math.floor(3.7) : </strong> <span id="floor"></span></p>
<p><strong>  3. Math.ceil(-42.3) : </strong> <span id="ceil"></span></p>
<p><strong>  4. Math.abs(-42.3) : </strong> <span id="abs"></span></p>
<p><strong>  5. Math.min(10,39,54,3,52):</strong> <span id="min"></span></p>
<p><strong>  6. Math.max(10,39,54,3,52):</strong> <span id="max"></span></p>
<p><strong>  7. Math.pow(2,3):</strong> <span id="pow"></span></p>
<p><strong>  8. Math.log10(10):</strong> <span id="log"></span></p>
<p><strong>  9. Math.sqrt(49):</strong> <span id="sqrt"></span></p>
</div>
<script>
let str=" web programming";
document.getElementById('len').innerHTML = str.length;
document.getElementById('up').innerHTML = str.toUpperCase();
document.getElementById('low').innerHTML = str.toLowerCase();
document.getElementById('c_at').innerHTML = str.charAt(2);
document.getElementById('str').innerHTML = str[3];
document.getElementById('index').innerHTML = str.indexOf("programming");
document.getElementById('slice').innerHTML = str.slice(5,);
document.getElementById('split').innerHTML = str.split(" ");
let str1="Good"
let str2="Morning"
document.getElementById('concat').innerHTML = str1.concat(" ",str2);
document.getElementById('repeat').innerHTML = str.repeat(3);
document.getElementById('replace').innerHTML = str.replace("web","C");  document.getElementById('round').textContent = Math.round(3.7);
document.getElementById('floor').textContent = Math.floor(3.7);   
document.getElementById('ceil').textContent =Math.ceil(-42.3);
document.getElementById('abs').textContent = Math.abs(-42.3);
document.getElementById('min').textContent = Math.min(10,39,54,3,52);
document.getElementById('max').textContent = Math.max(10,39,54,3,52);
document.getElementById('pow').textContent = Math.pow(2,3);
document.getElementById('log').textContent = Math.log10(10);
document.getElementById('sqrt').textContent = Math.sqrt(49);
</script>
